messages.welcomeDataModal.introductionText:
The new, native-web ElastiCube Manager introduces a smart visual approach to
						simplify data management. Before you start, here are a few things to keep in mind.
messages.welcomeDataModal.introductionTextTrail:
The new, native-web ElastiCube Manager introduces a smart visual approach 
						to simplify data management. Before you start, here are a few things to keep in mind.
messages.welcomeDataModal.descriptionText:
ElastiCubes are compatible with both the desktop ElastiCube manager and the web version.
						However the web version supports working with the following connectors: mySQL, MS-SQL, PostGres and RedShift.
messages.welcomeDataModal.sideBySideText:
The desktop ElastiCube Manager is fully functional and you can keep on using it.
						All your ElastiCubes can be opened in both environments. To learn more
messages.welcomeDataModal.supportedFunctionalityT:
The web environment supports viewing data from any source, 
							but at this point adding new data is only supported from:
Additionally, a few capabilities are not yet available in the web.
messages.welcomeDataModal.supportedFunctionalityS: See the list of supported functionality here.
messages.welcomeDataModal.managingDataWebTextSec1: Sisense offers both a desktop and new web ElastiCube Manager. All your ElastiCubes can be opened in both environments.
messages.welcomeDataModal.managingDataWebTextSec2:
At this point, there are a few differences between available features in the two environments. 
						The web environment supports viewing data from any source, but for now adding new data is only supported for these sources:
messages.welcomeDataModal.moreAvailableDataConnec: Dozens of other data connectors are available in the desktop ElastiCube Manager.
messages.welcomeDataModal.managingDataSupportedDa: To see all supported data sources and learn how to work side-by-side
messages.welcomeDataModal.feedback: We would love to hear your feedback:
